title: For Sale:  Romanian SKS All original, All matching, very rare to come across, excellent metal,
postcontent: I was going to hold onto this but have decided to sell it instead. This is an all matching except one electro stencil forcematch by factory.  Even the stock matches the rifle.  It is all original from the factory included the Romanian Shellacking on the stock.  The bore is bright which is rare and the stock is sealed which is rare.  Normanlly these have huges gouges in the stock but this stocks imperfections are still covered by the factory shellacking.  The Romanian SKSs were rarely imported into the US and the ones that made it are usually non-matching, beat up, and shot out.  This is one of the rare ones.  Made in 1960, the Russians sent all of their original equipment to the Romanians after the Russians stopped sks production when the ak47 was introduced.  So the Romanian are built on all Russian tooling.  They are closer to the original Russian rifles than the Chinese, Yugo, or Albanian.  In fact these are basically EXACT copies.  I sold a nonmatching two weeks ago for 300 and it was bought up by a collector within an hour.  I'm pricing this one at 375 because is is such a fine example of a rare sks.  Cugir Made, arrow in triangle 1960, armslist won't let me post more detailed pics so email me for more.

title: For Sale:  Sig 556xi Swat
location: Grand Rapids / Kentwood, Grand Rapids, Michigan
postcontent:
Hello. For sale is my Sig 556xi Swat model. This is the newest version of the Sig 556 line of Gas piston rifles based on the SG 550 and the AK design. The upgrades from the older model include the full picatinny rail on top and full ambidextrous controls; Along with a three position gas valve that now has a suppressed setting. This rifle is fully modular and will accept different barrel lengths and also will shoot 7.62x39 and .300blk with the correct conversion kits from SIG. More information can be found here. http://www.sigevolution.com/sig556xi

More about the rifle:

I purchased this rifle brand new in September of this year (2014) It is a great rifle and I really love how smoothly and reliably it shoots. I do not have the cheek riser or the Ar-15 style grip that it came with because I was going for the authentic swiss type look. To achieve that I added Troy Micro folding battle sights $(150). This sights sit a little lower than standard Ar sights and they are perfect for this rifle due to the dip in the Swiss style stock; They match up to form a perfect fit. I also have added the authentic Sig Swiss grip as it flowed with the rifle better and provides a more stable grip. 

The ;ight black finish on the gas block which is attached to the barrel has a little wear along the edges from general use and disassembly for cleaning. Also there are a few light scratches on the upper receiver (no dents) from use in the woods, shooting prone and doing drills and also setting the rifle down on tables and benches at the range. This rifle is in great overall shape and looks great.

This rifle has been flawless for me so far and I have not experienced any malfunctions whatsoever, with various types of ammunition; it just works and works, just like an AK. I have had it out in the woods and to the range a few times and accuracy has been very good. I have put exactly 270 rounds through this rifle. I hate to see it go but I have one to many in the safe and this one is the newest.

Since this is the Swat model it cost me about 1300 NIB. I am asking $900 due to the light scratching only and I am pretty firm on the price. I will meet at almost any FFL in the Grand Rapids area to conduct the transfer or may consider FTF in the Grand Rapids Area, although I prefer FFL. Cash only and no trades. If interested please contact me. Thanks for looking.
